# 7. 一緒に

Haruka: Chairman!
Chairman: Ah, MORE MORE JUMP! I apologize for having you all gather on such short notice.
Airi: That's okay. Are we really running short on bookmarks?
Operations Committee Member: Yes, more runners than we were expecting have applied, so it looks like we're not going to have enough to go around...
Chairman: We were hoping to give everybody one, but we may need to start considering a first-come-first-serve policy.
Operations Committee Member: It's such a shame. We were hoping everyone could go home with a beautiful little memory of our town.
Haruka: Oh...
Chairman: That's why we began holding the town marathon. Showing people just how beautiful this place is should help bring in more tourists and new residents...
Haruka: Pardon me!
Operations Committee Member: Huh?
Haruka: Can you tell us how many bookmarks we're currently short?
Operations Committee Member: How many? I'd say about 400 would cover it...
Haruka: Okay. A hundred per person, then.
Shizuku: Oh...
Shizuku: Hehe. You're right!
Operations Committee Member: Wait, what are you saying?
Airi: There's still enough time for each of us to make a hundred more. Then, we'll have enough for everyone.
Operations Committee Member: B-But! We couldn't possibly ask you to go that far...
Minori: It's okay! We're the ones who suggested that we pass out bookmarks in the first place!
Shizuku: Please let us do this. We want to put smiles on the faces of everyone in this town and all those who participate in the marathon.
Operations Committee Member: Girls...
Operations Committee Member: Then, please do. I'd love to help out, but we still have things to do for tomorrow.
Haruka: That's okay. You can leave this to us.
Haruka: Let's start by checking how many extra flowers we have. If we need more...
Chairman: I can ask the flower shop to see if they have the ones we're using. I'll do something about the budget.
Haruka: Thank you very much! In that case, we should be able to dry them out in time by using the microwave.
Haruka: Alright, Airi, Shizuku, could you two check our reserves and go with the chairman to get the flowers we need?
Shizuku: Okay!
Haruka: Minori, can you gather up all the tools so we can get started right away? I'll bring the materials.
Minori: Got it!
Saito: I'll help you carry everything!
Show Director: ... Keep the cameras rolling.
Crew Member: O-Of course!
Haruka: Phew...
Airi: Okay, that makes about twenty total.
Minori: Wow, that's a lot already! Though, we still have a long way to go until 400.
Minori: Alright, that means we gotta really get cracking!
Shizuku: Yes, but we should also make each one with care.
???: Oh, you're really going at it.
Haruka: Huh?
Operations Committee Members: Honestly, why didn't you come tell us?
Airi: Everyone! But what are you doing here?
Local A: We should be asking you that.
Haruka: Oh...
Local A: Are they sure about this? I mean, they're idols, right?
Haruka: We apologize for doing this without consulting you all, but...
Local A: If the chairman hadn't told us, then you would've ended up doing all the work.
Haruka: Huh?
Haruka: Wait, but...
Local C: Ah, don't look at us like that.
Local C: I understand why you'd be hesitant. We didn't exactly welcome you with open arms.
Local C: We thought you and that television crew were really just here for some feel-good footage.
Local C: But when we actually bothered looking...
Local B: You've all worked so hard for our town.
Local B: Even when the cameras weren't on, you got muddy harvesting crops and you built that big stage. I honestly couldn't believe my eyes.
Local B: But it made us really happy.
Haruka: Oh...
Local C: Besides, this is our town. That means it's our duty to act.
Local A: Right. What we mean to say is...
Local A: Let's do this, together.
Haruka: ...! Thank you very much.
Haruka: (That's so great to hear.)
Haruka: It's normal for them to be wary of outsiders and those they think they can't rely on. Their town is just that precious to them.
Haruka: So, it's up to us to be the best diplomats we can, to help ease their worries.
Shizuku: We have to take this marathon and our interactions with the locals very seriously. We need to show them that we're going to do our absolute best.
Haruka: (Our feelings made it through to them.)
Operations Committee Members: Oh, Haruka, your flowers are lined up so nicely. Can you show me how to do that?
Haruka: Thank you. You see, even if the flowers stick out a little at first, they'll shrink into position like this.
Operations Committee Members: Oh, so that's the trick!
Haruka: Also, you don't necessarily have to line them up in a row. You can actually layer them together too...
